Stack: Next.js 15 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind, Framer Motion, Stripe

═══════════════════════════════════════════
VISUAL DIRECTION — reference: Bottega Veneta homepage
═══════════════════════════════════════════

HOMEPAGE HERO:
- Full viewport height, full bleed — image or video edge to edge, no padding
- Navbar floats transparently over the hero — white text, no background
- NO large hero headline on first load — let the visual breathe
- After 1.2s: ONE line of Bodoni text fades in at lower center
  Example: "Worn in. Never out."  or  "Leather that remembers."
- Two ghost CTA buttons near bottom center (like BV layout):
  [  Discover the Collection  ]  [  Shop Jackets  ]
- Thin white borders on CTAs, Inter label-size text, spaced caps
- On scroll: hero fades, next section appears

OVERALL SITE FEEL:
- Cinematic. Slow. Intentional. Every element earns its place.
- Generous negative space — when in doubt, add more breathing room
- Images always full-bleed or large — never small thumbnails
- Text is sparse — one strong line beats three weak ones
- No decorative elements, no icons in headings, no gradients

DARK/LIGHT BALANCE:
- Homepage: dark first (void #0D0C0A background)
- Product pages: can mix — dark hero, light product info panel
- Journal/About: parchment (#F5F2EC) background — intentional contrast
- The switch from dark to light signals a content shift to the visitor

TYPOGRAPHY RULES:
- Bodoni Moda: only for headlines, product names, section titles (24px+)
- Bodoni italic: for emotional sublines, taglines, pull quotes
- Inter light (300): all body copy
- Inter medium (500): navigation, labels, buttons — all caps, wide tracking
- Never use Bodoni below 24px — hairlines disappear

COLOR RULES:
- Primary bg: #0D0C0A (void) — not pure black, warm undertone
- Primary text: #F5F2EC (parchment) — not pure white
- Accent: #8B5E3C (leather) — used sparingly: underlines, cart count, dividers
- Borders: #2A2825 — very subtle, almost invisible
- Never use generic blue, red, or green anywhere on the site

ANIMATION RULES:
- Ease: cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.1, 0.25, 1) — always
- Duration: 600-1200ms for reveals, 300-400ms for hovers
- Direction: elements fade UP into place (translateY 24px → 0)
- Stagger: when multiple elements reveal, 80-120ms between each
- Always wrap Framer Motion in useReducedMotion() check
- Never bounce, never overshoot, never spin — all motion is calm

